S5.description:
📚 Hi, everyone! Welcome to the Study Squad!

Hi all, I'm Endrit, 29 years old (in my 16th year, haha, just a joke!), a medical student studying in lovely Italy.
The gadget you can see above my glasses is the Luminette Light Therapy Glasses—it replicates the effect of sunlight to enhance your energy and concentration.

I really think that studying can be made easier and more enjoyable with good company. And so, I'm here for the purpose of connecting, inspiring, and growing with all of you. Let's make studying a positive, rewarding, and perhaps even enjoyable thing.

🕒 Daily Streams
I stream nearly daily, 12+ hours of 60/10 Pomodoro sessions.
Start time: around 11:00–11:30 a.m. (UTC+1).
I will put up an advance notice on YouTube if I am unable to stream.

🌐 Join the Community:
Be a part of our friendly and supportive Discord community:
👉 https://discord.gg/aKVAGV2R46
Don't hesitate to send a friend request—let's connect and support one another!

💡 Credits:
My incredible Discord configuration was designed by my talented buddy Haris.
(For business inquiries, remember—I get a cut 😄)

Let's make the most out of this journey—a Pomodoro at a time!

이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다. 

군대 후배의 추천으로 법무사에 도전하게 되었고, 쿠팡 퇴사 후 2021년 8월 말부터 법무사 1차 공부를 시작해서, 1년 만에 집에서 인강으로 22년 법무사 1차 시험에 합격하였고, 당해 2차 시험은 130명 안에 들지 못했습니다. 23년에 2차 공부를 후회없이 하였지만 불합격했습니다. 새로운 마음으로 재동차 도전중입니다. 같이 힘내요🔥🔥🔥

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

S48.title: 50대 감정평가사 도전기! 12HR-STUDY WITH ME (스터디 윗미)/공무원 시험/수험생/전문직 시험/혼자 공부/캠스터디/Huntington Beach/채팅은 쉬는시간에~ 2025-05-30 13:35
S48.description:
50대에 접어들게 되면서....
감히 감정평가사라는 정말 어려운 시험에 도전하게 되었습니다.
서울대, 연고대 출신 합격생이 가장 많고, 
8천여명중에 150~200여명 안팎의 인원만 합격하는 극악의 난이도의 시험입니다.
50대는 1년에 보통 전국에서 2~3명 내외로 합격하더군요....
그런 똑똑하고 체력좋은 젊은 20대~30대 친구들한테 제가 무모한 싸움을 걸었네요.
몸과 머리가 젊을때 같지않지만, 절실함 하나만을 가지고 시작했습니다!
유튜브 공부법은 약하디 약한 저의 의지를 바로 잡는데 꼭 필요한 장치인것 같습니다.
매일매일 이해하지 못하고 암기하지 못함에서 오는 
'불합격하면 어떡하지??'라는 극악의 불안감이 엄습해오지만...
꼭 이겨내겠습니다!
올해 4월 1차, 내년 7월 2차 시험 합격을 목표로 달려가고 있습니다.
저를 아시던 모르시던 한번씩 들어오셔서
*구독, 좋아요 눌러주시고*
[공부 잘하고 있는지 확인해 주시고] 
[만약 나약한 모습을 보인다면 쓴소리해주세요] 
부탁드립니다!!
마지막으로, 
여기 들어 오시는 모든 분들이 준비하시는 시험에 꼭 합격하시길 기원드립니다.
감사합니다!!

As I entered my 50s...
I dare to take a very difficult exam called a certified public appraiser.
It's an extremely difficult exam that only about 150~200 out of 8,000 passed every year in Korea.
Usually, only two or three people in their 50s pass the test a year...
I started a reckless fight against those smart, energetic young people in their 20s and 30s.
My body and head aren't like when I was young, but I started with only one desperation!
The YouTube study method seems to be a necessary device to strengthen my weak will.
Everyday i'm worried that I might fail the exam, but I'll overcome it!
I am studying hard with the goal of passing the first test in April this year. 
and the second exam (Final) in July next year.
Whether you know me or not, please come in.
*Please press subscribe and like*
And please check if I am studying well.
If I don't study or show a weak mental state, please say something bitter.
Please!
Lastly, I hope this real-time streaming will be of great help to your studies.
Thank you!!

S56.title: Study with me for 9 hours - (🔴 LIVE  | ⏱️ 50/10 timer | No music) 2025-05-30 13:35
S56.description:
Ciao friends! I'm Kevin and here you can see me progress and join me in the deed.

I've always been uncomfortable exposing myself, yet here I am, and you might be asking yourself why in 2021 I started streaming my a-- sitting hours when I could do the same off-camera.

The honest reason is, I've been struggling with procrastination for a long time, and despite I could always achieve the expected results I wanted more and I found my solution in the Hawthorne effect, basically "if you are watched, your behavior changes in response to being observed" thus making you more productive and performant.

POOF! The procrastination curse was broken. I was - magically? - able to put in hours of focus on a certain activity without following any butterfly in the process, without any distraction from my mind.
If you want to try the Hawthorne effect on you as I did, you can tell me in chat and join me on Discord (so you can go live with me): https://discord.gg/VPnEJd6PWA.

Not only I could now focus, but I'd also gained confidence in exposing myself in the social field, meeting many wonderful people with whom we shared and keep sharing thoughts and personal events, and laugh together, and whom I can for real call friends.
A *BIG* heartfelt THANK goes to YOU ❤️, as without a viewer there would be no Hawthorne effect and no friends to chat with - there would be no progress.


How do "study with me lives" work?
There are 50/10 Pomodoro timers, where each session is made of 50 minutes of studying/working (progress time) and 10 minutes of chatting/moving (break time).

What are you working on?
I'm either studying medicine or coding.

Do you like pineapple pizza?
No.

Have you even ever tried it?
A fruit on a pizza is wrong. If you want pineapple on something get a damn fruit salad.

S75.description:
Welcome to Study With Me Shiva! 🌟

🔴 Live Study Session – 06:00 AM to 06:40 PM

🌅 Day 18 of 90! Let’s kickstart this 90-day study challenge with a 6-hour deep study session using the 120/40 Pomodoro Technique – 120 minutes of focused studying followed by a 40-minute break. Stay consistent, stay motivated, and let’s crush our goals together! 💪📚

📚 10-Hour Study Plan (120/40 Rule) ⏳
🕕 06:00 AM - 08:00 AM → Study Session 1 
☕ 08:00 AM - 08:40 AM → Break 
🕣 08:40 AM - 10:40 AM → Study Session 2 
🍎 10:40 AM - 11:20 AM → Break 
🕚 11:20 AM - 01:20 PM → Study Session 3 
🍛 01:20 PM - 02:00 PM → Break (Lunch & Rest) 
🕑 02:00 PM - 04:00 PM → Study Session 4 
☕ 04:00 PM - 04:40 PM → Break 
🕟 04:40 PM - 06:40 PM → Study Session 5

💡 10 Hours of Pure Focus! Let's Crush It! 🚀📚🔥

💡 Motivation Tips to Stay Focused:
✨ Start with a goal – Write down what you want to achieve in this session.
🎯 Eliminate distractions – Keep your phone on silent & focus mode ON!
🚀 Stay consistent – Small daily efforts lead to BIG results.
💪 Push through the tough moments – Every session counts, keep going!
📖 Review & Reflect – After the session, take notes on what you learned.

⚠️ Note: Sunday’s live session is uncertain. I will update if I go live on Sundays.

💬 Let’s stay productive together! Drop a comment on what you're studying. Let’s achieve greatness! 🚀🔥

✨ Why Join?
Motivation: Stay inspired with consistent study sessions that keep you on track.
Focus: With the Pomodoro technique, you’ll find the perfect balance between intense focus and regular breaks.
Community: Connect with like-minded learners and become part of a supportive study community.
Productivity: Achieve more in less time with structured sessions that make studying efficient and fun!

💻 My Gadgets:
Laptop: Lenovo Ideapad 5
Mouse: Lenovo Bluetooth Mouse
Study Lamp: Eveready Study Lamp
Camera: Realme 5 Pro Mobile

🔔 Don't forget to subscribe!
Be part of my daily study sessions, get notified of upcoming live sprints, and let’s learn together. Subscribe, turn on notifications, and join the #studywithmeshiva  community.

S92.description:
This stream is for the final stretch — the last few days before your exam. You don’t need more anxiety or pressure. What you need is a calm, consistent rhythm to help you actually get things done. That’s what this 45/15 Pomodoro study session gives you. We’ll work in 45-minute focus blocks followed by 15-minute rest breaks, so your mind can stay sharp, but not exhausted. Whether you're reviewing notes, solving practice questions, or rewriting concepts to memorize — this stream is your study zone. No distractions, no talking, just real structure and support through visuals, beats, and rhythm. You’ve already done more than you think. Let’s make these final sessions count together.

Отлично подходит для повторения конспектов, проработки заданий, подготовки по темам. Без разговоров, без отвлекающих факторов — только ты, твои цели и поток.
